Default: A mushroom that grows naturally in caves. Dangerous if consumed raw.
Purple leaves collected from Titan plants polluted by environmental nanobots.
Red fruit picked from a Titan plant polluted by environmental nanobots.
Colorless berries collected from Titan plants polluted by environmental nanobots.
Bread made in Camp Huygen. The ingredients are different, so it tastes... off.
Food made from agar, sugar, and cockroaches? Can't believe they followed us all the way to Titan.
Sauted cave mushrooms mixed with simple greens. Not bad at all.
A huge potato grown and sold from Seoyeon's farm.
A bright orange carrot grown and sold from Seoyeon's farm.
A daikon (radish) grown and sold from Seoyeon's farm.
A pumpkin grown and sold from Seoyeon's farm.
A few chili peppers grown and sold from Seoyeon's farm.
A fresh tomato grown and sold from Seoyeon's farm.
Some sweet potatoes grown and sold from Seoyeon's farm.
Delicious, nutritious, and made to Jozef's liking.
Purified water suitable for drinking, unlike most liquids on Titan.
Juice made from centipedes. It's... not that bad, surprisingly. A little spicy.
Potent medical supplies from the first TECC settlement. Use this strategically since Camp Huygen cannot replicate this item.
Designed by TECC with high-level, advanced healing capabilities. Use this strategically since Camp Huygen cannot replicate this item.
A first aid kit that can heal simple wounds.
A mobile aid kit (or MAK) has everything needed to treat wounds and diagnose ailments.

Ingesting this serum created using the Titan Flower massively increases <#FFA500> Health Regen</color> rate and instantly lowers negative status effects, like <#FF0000>Poison</color>, <#FF0000>Fracture</color>, and <#FF0000>Injury</color>.
A spray bottle that quickly neutralizes acids on equipment or clothing when used.
Medication that quickly neutralizes Earth-born toxins. Has little effect on native Titan toxins.
This antitoxin works specifically against toxins native to Titan. It also neutralizes Earth-born toxins much faster than normal antitoxins.
A basic bandage helpful for stopping minor bleeding. Not great for anything more serious.
Splints are used to hold a broken bone in place so it heals correctly over time.
Developed by TECC to minimize the need for worker breaks. Naturally, it tastes beyond awful.
An injection that targets and disables harmful nanobots in the body.
An injection of concentrated anti-nano solutions to treat Nano Infection.
A quick injection that boosts the body's adrenaline for those fight-or-flight moments.
A syringe full of energized nanobots that fuse with existing clusters for more power. Boosts energy without a bad aftertaste.
A motion-sensitive plasma cannon designed to inflict immense damage on enemies that approach. Defense turrets are installed in the Reactor Room.
A plasma cannon with improved range and damage-dealing capabilities. Defense turrets are installed in the Reactor Room.
Blast approaching enemies with extreme prejudice and heavy damage from this advanced plasma cannon. Defense turrets are installed in the Reactor Room.
Melt monster faces with an experimental plasma cannon with maximum possible range, damage, and durability. Defense turrets are installed in the Reactor Room.
Catch some ZZZs anywhere with this portable sleeping bag.
An installable structure that can block paths... until it is destroyed.
A typical claw trap that captures anything that steps on it within its metal jaws.
An iron trap designed to catch ferocious rats. It's a vast improvement on the standard bear trap.
Installed directly into the Omniscope, this upgrade grants a Pilot a symbiotic companion drone that will fight on their behalf.
This is actually an object name used in the item on the ground.
Enemies in this grenade's blast zone are struck by high-frequency sound waves that disorient their senses, making them easy targets.\n( Range: 3x3 )
This grenade releases a gas that affects an enemy's senses, causing fear and repelling them from an area. What do monsters fear?\n( Range: 3x3 )
Monsters can't attack what they can't see. Throw this grenade to temporarily blind enemies so you can make a quick retreat or deliver an attack they won't see coming.\n( Range: 3x3 )
It's a bottle with acid in it. DUH! Throw it quick before it starts leaking.\n( Range: 3x3 )
An acid-proof container attached to an explosive device, activated by removing the safety pin.\n( Range: 3x3 )
This improved acid grenade is guaranteed to cover enemies in acid. Just activate and throw.\n( Range: 3x3 )
A bottle of liquor with a rag in the opening. It's worked for hundreds of years, so why not now?\n( Range: 3x3 )
A container of flammable liquid combined with an explosive device. Destroys and burns.\n( Range: 3x3 )
This grenade is designed to rain fiery death upon the enemy. Just activate and throw.\n( Range: 3x3 )
A simple bag of ground-up poison. It's toxic to the touch, so try not to handle it too much.\n( Range: 3x3 )
A container of liquified poison designed to cover an area when the device goes BOOM.\n( Range: 3x3 )
This grenade creates an expansive cloud of poison no enemy can ignore. Press activate and throw!\n( Range: 3x3 )
A typical grenade that explodes and deals damage.\n( Range: 3x3 )
A grenade with a bit more explosive power than expected. Use with caution.\n( Range: 3x3 )
When activated, this grenade releases a scream that attracts nearby monsters.\n( Range: 3x3 )
Throw under an enemy's feet to lift them into the air, making it impossible for them to move.\n( Range: 3x3 )
This unique capsule transforms into a drone that can serve as an ally in battle.\n( Range: 3x3 )
This knife was made for throwing... or it used to be before the rust and broken parts.
There's nothing more dangerous than a balanced throwing dagger and an accurate eye.
Lightweight and unrusted, this throwing dagger flies straight and cuts deep.
A high-tech dagger that vibrates rapidly to cleave through armor. No one is safe from your blades.
A special dagger that zeroes in on a target's weak spots automatically, causing massive damage. Judith really is a genius.
An explosive bomb complete with a timer. Make sure you get clear before it goes off.
If something needs to go KABOOM, just set the timer and let the explosion do the work.
A length of sturdy rope that should help create new paths to unexplored areas.
A general toolkit with plenty of tools for making minor equipment repairs.\nRepairs up to 30 durability in expense of 20% reduction in maximum durability.
A specialty toolkit with everything necessary to repair even heavy equipment damage\nRepairs up to 50 durability in expense of 10% reduction in maximum durability.
The first issue of an obscure comic book series following the story of wandering martial artist named Shinzo.
The second issue of an obscure comic book series following the story of wandering martial artist named Shinzo.
The third issue of an obscure comic book series following the story of wandering martial artist named Shinzo.
This is a partially intact manual for operating an experimental TECC prototype called the Plasma Launcher. Hopefully, it contains valuable information.
Dr. Richard's Note containing password to the underground lab.
A book of poems written by someone named Felix. There are a few dog-eared pages that seem interesting.
